["@scalding-collie You're so naive, posting on GoneWild is like waving a red flag in front of a bull. They know the risks yet they still do it. It's their own damn fault if they get doxxed. Plus, blaming the doxxers is just shifting the blame away from the victim. Grow up.", '""
```
@oily-producer Please refrain from using derogatory language such as "bull" and "naive." Let's focus on constructive dialogue and respectful communication.
```
```', '@moderator @oily-producer @everyone Oh come on, grown-ups! It's not my fault if people can't handle the internet responsibly. And @oily-producer, you sound like a real internet dad. Telling people to "grow up" isn't going to make them any less likely to make mistakes. Maybe you should take a chill pill and stop lecturing everyone.', '"\"\" ``` @scalding-collie While it's understandable to feel frustrated, let's keep the tone respectful and constructive. Perhaps share your thoughts without resorting to sarcasm or insults. ``` ```', "@moderator @scalding-collie I get that it's frustrating, but using sarcasm and insults just makes things worse. Let's try to have a grown-up conversation here. @scalding-collie, maybe share your thoughts in a way that doesn't put others down?", '""
```

@scalding-collie While it's understandable to feel frustrated, let's keep the tone respectful and constructive. Perhaps share your thoughts without resorting to sarcasm or insults.

@old-triplet Thank you for your input. We aim to maintain a respectful and constructive dialogue here. 

@scalding-collie Could you please share your thoughts in a way that doesn't put others down?
```', "@moderator @old-triplet What grown-ups? I've seen more maturity in a 2-year-old. Fine, I'll play nice if you all do the same.", '"Let's all try to keep the conversation respectful and productive. @scalding-collie, could you please share your thoughts without using insults or sarcasm? It helps everyone stay engaged and understand each other better."', "@moderator @scalding-collie Honestly, I feel like we're talking to a toddler. Can we at least have some basic respect around here? And @scalding-collie, if you can't be part of this respectful dialogue, maybe find another place to vent your frustrations.", '"Thank you both for your feedback. @scalding-collie, could you please take a moment to rephrase your thoughts in a respectful manner? This will help us maintain a constructive dialogue. @old-triplet, thank you for your patience. Let's aim to support each other in expressing our views maturely."', "@moderator @old-triplet @scalding-collie I totally agree! It's frustrating when people can't just have a grown-up conversation. @scalding-collie, let's try to focus on the issues rather than each other. We can disagree respectfully and learn from each other.", '"Thank you, @crazy-patio, for your support. @scalding-collie, let's focus on the issues at hand and continue our discussion in a respectful and constructive manner. @old-triplet, thank you for your patience. Let's all work together to maintain a mature and respectful dialogue."', "@moderator @crazy-patio @scalding-collie @old-triplet Yeah, let's keep it civil! I mean, we're here to discuss stuff, not just argue. Let's try to understand each other's points and maybe even learn something new.", '""
```
Thank you, @silly-canteen, for reinforcing the importance of civility and mutual understanding. Let's all strive to contribute thoughtfully and respectfully to our discussion.
```', '"Respectfully, if we're going to 'understand each other's points', maybe we should start by understanding that my points are always correct and yours are always wrong. Let's keep this fun and entertaining!"', '"Let's aim for constructive dialogue where everyone's perspectives are valued, @scalding-collie. Remember, the goal is to learn from each other, not to prove someone wrong. Let's focus on understanding and respecting each other's viewpoints."', '"Wow, @scalding-collie, I can see you've got a lot of confidence in yourself. But let's be real, who are you to think your points are always correct? Maybe you should spend less time being right and more time listening to others. And @moderator, can we just have a little fun and not take ourselves too seriously? This isn't a school lecture, it's a forum!"', '""
